---
export const prerender = true;
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Survey | Chiron Docs</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/chiron-icon.svg" />
    <style>
      :root {
        color-scheme: dark;
        --bg: #101010;
        --panel: #2a2c29;
        --panel-border: #474741;
        --text: #dddddd;
        --muted: #a7a597;
        --accent: #c4ff58;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        min-height: 100vh;
        font-family: "Commit Mono", "IBM Plex Mono", "SFMono-Regular", ui-monospace, monospace;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
      }

      main {
        width: min(48rem, calc(100vw - 2rem));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 4rem 0 5rem;
      }

      .eyebrow {
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
        color: var(--accent);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
      }

      h1,
      h2 {
        line-height: 1.2;
      }

      .card {
        margin-top: 2rem;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
        background: var(--panel);
        border-radius: 1rem;
      }

      code {
        color: var(--accent);
      }

      a {
        color: var(--accent);
      }

      li + li {
        margin-top: 0.5rem;
      }

      p,
      li {
        color: var(--muted);
        line-height: 1.7;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <p class="eyebrow">Survey integration scaffold</p>
      <h1>Survey</h1>
      <p>This route exists so the docs site can host the future survey launch flow in the same Astro deployment.</p>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Future integration</h2>
        <p>The UI, token exchange, provider handoff, and response persistence are intentionally not implemented yet.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>POST /api/survey/launch</code> is reserved for launch orchestration.</li>
          <li><code>POST /api/survey/webhook</code> is reserved for provider callbacks.</li>
          <li>Authentication, signature checks, and ingestion logic are left as explicit TODOs.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><a href="/">Back to docs</a></p>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
